Problem 1

Explain in your own words:

Why are containers better than VMs for microservices?

Containers are better for microservices because:

• Microservices require fast startup & scaling → containers start in milliseconds
• They allow independent deployment of each service
• They ensure environment consistency across dev, staging, prod
• They are lightweight, so you can run many services on the same node
• They integrate easily with orchestration tools like Kubernetes

Key Insight:

Microservices = many small services → containers fit perfectly.
